OL,3,CFrom Harry Potter to SpongeBob see how
OL,4,Cthe North West's marking World Book Day
OL,6,FFigures from the National Literacy
OL,7,FTrust show that last year children's
OL,8,Fdaily reading rates fell to their
OL,9,Flowest levels in 20 years, with only 1
OL,10,Fin 3 of 8 to 18-year-olds enjoying
OL,11,Freading and under 1 in 5 reading daily.
OL,13,FAlmost thirty years after the first
OL,14,FHarry Potter book was published the
OL,15,Fyoung wizard created by J.K Rowling
OL,16,Fremains a popular choice. The series
OL,17,Fand films had been credited with
OL,18,Fgetting young people back into reading.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
